##Notes for Week 7: 3.1 When Marginal Revenue is Less than Price

The companies are constrained by downward sloping of the law of demand. And that's what makes the company produce less, and that what makes the situation a little more complicated.

Follow this using the hypothetical that now the price is not constant, but it actually decreases, when the quantity increase:

